The paper deals with the study of approximate LDCs, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The problem involves finding a set of points in high-dimensional space, which suggests computational geometry (cs.CG) as a possible sub-category. The use of lower bounds suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the study of LDCs is closely related to coding theory (cs.CC).
